name: System
description: Contains methods for system operations, such as writing debug messages and scheduling jobs.

abortjob(string).name: abortJob
abortjob(string).description: Stops the specified job. The stopped job is still visible in the job queue in the Salesforce user interface.

assert(boolean,object).name: assert
assert(boolean,object).signature: public static void assert(Boolean condition, Object msg)
assert(boolean,object).description: Asserts that the specified condition is true. If it is not, a fatal error is returned that causes code execution to halt.

assertequals(object,object,object).name: assertEquals
assertequals(object,object,object).signature: public static void assertEquals(Object expected, Object actual, Object msg)
assertequals(object,object,object).description: Asserts that the first two arguments are the same. If they are not, a fatal error is returned that causes code execution to halt.

assertnotequals(object,object,object).name: assertNotEquals
assertnotequals(object,object,object).signature: public static void assertNotEquals(Object expected, Object actual, Object msg)
assertnotequals(object,object,object).description: Asserts that the first two arguments are different. If they are the same, a fatal error is returned that causes code execution to halt.

currentpagereference().name: currentPageReference
currentpagereference().description: Returns a reference to the current page. This is used with Visualforce pages.

currenttimemillis().name: currentTimeMillis
currenttimemillis().description: Returns the current time in milliseconds, which is expressed as the difference between the current time and midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC.

debug(object).name: debug
debug(object).description: Writes the specified message, in string format, to the execution debug log. The DEBUG log level is used.

debug(logginglevel,object).name: debug
debug(logginglevel,object).signature: public static void debug(LoggingLevel logLevel, Object msg)
debug(logginglevel,object).description: Writes the specified message, in string format, to the execution debug log with the specified log level.

enqueuejob(object).name: enqueueJob
enqueuejob(object).description: Adds a job to the Apex job queue that corresponds to the specified queueable class and returns the job ID.

equals(object,object).name: equals
equals(object,object).signature: public static Boolean equals(Object obj1, Object obj2)
equals(object,object).description: Returns true if both arguments are equal. Otherwise, returns false.

getapplicationreadwritemode().name: getApplicationReadWriteMode
getapplicationreadwritemode().description: Returns the read write mode set for an organization during Salesforce.com upgrades and downtimes.

hashcode(object).name: hashCode
hashcode(object).description: Returns the hash code of the specified object.

isbatch().name: isBatch
isbatch().description: Returns true if a batch Apex job invoked the executing code, or false if not. In API version 35.0 and earlier, also returns true if a queueable Apex job invoked the code.

isfuture().name: isFuture
isfuture().description: Returns true if the currently executing code is invoked by code contained in a method annotated with future; false otherwise.

isqueueable().name: isQueueable
isqueueable().description: Returns true if a queueable Apex job invoked the executing code. Returns false if not, including if a batch Apex job or a future method invoked the code.

isscheduled().name: isScheduled
isscheduled().description: Returns true if the currently executing code is invoked by a scheduled Apex job; false otherwise.

movepassword(id,id).name: movePassword
movepassword(id,id).signature: public static void movePassword(ID targetUserId, ID sourceUserId)
movepassword(id,id).description: Moves the specified user’s password to a different user.

now().name: now
now().description: Returns the current date and time in the GMT time zone.

process(list).name: process
process(list).description: Processes the list of work item IDs.

purgeoldasyncjobs(date).name: purgeOldAsyncJobs
purgeoldasyncjobs(date).description: Deletes asynchronous Apex job records for jobs that have finished execution before the specified date with a Completed, Aborted, or Failed status, and returns the number of records deleted.

requestversion().name: requestVersion
requestversion().description: Returns a two-part version that contains the major and minor version numbers of a package.

resetpassword(id,boolean).name: resetPassword
resetpassword(id,boolean).signature: public static System.ResetPasswordResult resetPassword(ID userId, Boolean sendUserEmail)
resetpassword(id,boolean).description: Resets the password for the specified user.

resetpasswordwithemailtemplate(id,boolea.name: resetPasswordWithEmailTemplate
resetpasswordwithemailtemplate(id,boolea.signature: public static System.ResetPasswordResult resetPasswordWithEmailTemplate(Id userId, Boolean sendUserEmail, String emailTemplateName)
resetpasswordwithemailtemplate(id,boolea.description: Resets the user's password and sends an email to the user with their new password. You specify the email template that is sent to the specified user. Use this method for external users of communities.

runas(system.version).name: runAs
runas(system.version).description: Changes the current package version to the package version specified in the argument.

runas(user).name: runAs
runas(user).description: Changes the current user to the specified user.

schedule(string,string,object).name: schedule
schedule(string,string,object).signature: public static String schedule(String jobName, String cronExpression, Object schedulableClass)
schedule(string,string,object).description: Use schedule with an Apex class that implements the Schedulable interface to schedule the class to run at the time specified by a Cron expression.

schedulebatch(database.batchable,string,.name: scheduleBatch
schedulebatch(database.batchable,string,.signature: public static String scheduleBatch(Database.Batchable batchable, String jobName, Integer minutesFromNow)
schedulebatch(database.batchable,string,.description: Schedules a batch job to run once in the future after the specified time interval and with the specified job name.

schedulebatch(database.batchable,string,.name: scheduleBatch
schedulebatch(database.batchable,string,.signature: public static String scheduleBatch(Database.Batchable batchable, String jobName, Integer minutesFromNow, Integer scopeSize)
schedulebatch(database.batchable,string,.description: Schedules a batch job to run once in the future after the specified the time interval, with the specified job name and scope size. Returns the scheduled job ID (CronTrigger ID).

setpassword(id,string).name: setPassword
setpassword(id,string).signature: public static void setPassword(ID userId, String password)
setpassword(id,string).description: Sets the password for the specified user.

submit(list).name: submit
submit(list).description: Submits the processed approvals. The current user is the submitter and the entry criteria is evaluated for all processes applicable to the current user.

today().name: today
today().description: Returns the current date in the current user's time zone.
